This launcher uses this version of Minecraft Legacy Console Edition: https://github.com/smartcmd/MinecraftConsoles/releases/tag/nightly

This launcher installs Minecraft Legacy Console Edition if you never installed it, or it updates your current Legacy Console Edition if a newer version is available.
You can boot into the game once done installing/updating, or at any time you open it as long as it's installed.
You can choose where you save Legacy Console Edition, and it remembers the location when you load back into it later.

This Launcher makes sure these are unaffected while updating:

- Saves
- Settings
- UID
- Options
- Username

Video of launcher in action: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d2NIHyg9rNU

Download here: https://github.com/Lucario4LyfeYT/Minecraft-Consoles-Launcher/releases/tag/Standalone_Legacy_Launcher
